<p>Consider a collection of Users:</p>  <pre><code>{ name: 'Jeff' } { name: 'Joel' } </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to efficiently get all the unique values for <code>name</code>? </p>  <pre><code>User.pluck(:name).uniq </code></pre>  <p>To return </p>  <pre><code>[ 'Jeff', 'Joel' ] </code></pre>  <p>I think this would get the whole collection, so it would be inefficient. </p>  <p>However, if there is an index on <code>name</code>, is there a way to get all the unique values without getting all the documents? </p>  <p>Or is there another way to efficiently get the unique <code>names</code>?</p>